lieved to have studied in Egypt.\n</p>\n',5,'nsd9N3kfXX',13,'2020-05-22 16:46:23','2020-07-09 18:16:52',0),(48,'The Rebellion ',1,'\n<p>The difficulty is determining when the rebellion occurred.\nIndeed Noah\'s flood was to end all the decedents of the Watchers and human women.\nYet, the flood did not kill and the descendants of the Watchers.\nAt least one survived.\n</p><p>\nGiven that the rebellion lists more that a dozen angles, I am incline to say Sumar was the recipient of their knowledge.\nThe root culture of Sumer seems to come from India and would not have had the baggage that other cultures in the Middle East would have had towards the Watchers. \nIt is of course possible that this rebellion happened more than one time with the story of Enoch simply an amalgamation of various stories into one as the Bible writers were want to do.\n</p><p>\nCuriously, there is a tradition that Mount Hermon on the border between Lebanon and Syria that the oath that the fallen watchers was sworn.\nThe highest temple in the ancient world known as Qasr Antar had a limestone stele that was translated to say \'According to the command of the greatest a(nd) Holy God, those who take an oath (proceed) from here.\'.\nSuch a statement using the phrase \'greatest a(nd) Holy God\' does not seem like the oath that the watchers would have used.\nIt does raise questions as to who and what oath is mentioned especially in light of the nickname for the mountain as the \'mountain of oath\'\nPerhaps it was here that newly christened watchers took their oath and began their journey to where they would serve.\n</p>\n',0,'zANssQus6z',15,'2020-05-22 16:46:24','2020-05-22 16:46:24',0),(49,'The Issue of Numbers ',1,'\n<p>Increasing population had brought a significant number of men for the Watch.\nEnoch\'s story of the Watchers/angles/sons of god was just that a rebellion of individuals who traditionally were solitary due to lack of population.  \nAs population increased, the Watchers moved into the towns to work by creating a building with high wall that lean outwards to reflect the light from fires upward.\nThe building had two large platforms at the bottom and no roof.\nWith this development, a Watcher could live anywhere after an initial instruction in what to do and how.\nI believe that the first buildings created by the Watchers where the towers in town such as Jerico.\n</p>\n',1,'L96d42MKAT',15,'2020-05-22 16:46:24','2020-05-22 16:46:24',0),(50,'The Fall of Greece ',1,'\n<p>With the fall of the city-states in Greece, the places where a free exchange of ideas fell as well.\nGreece standing at the crossroads between Europe and Asia Minor has a history of transitory people. \nFrom the people with Aegean roots with Anatolian farming techniques in 6,000 BC to the waves of people coming down from Europe during droughts, Greece has been a country of change.\n</p><p>\nGreece is interesting because of the story of Olympus where the Gods reside.\nThe legions of the demi-gods which sounds like the Nephilim.\nThe story of Hercules illustrates the dangers of the Watchers and their offspring.\n</p>\n',2,'qvBdQaHQm8',15,'2020-05-22 16:46:24','2020-05-22 16:46:24',0),(51,'The Threat of Rome ',1,'\n<p>Rome had a way of making everything Roman.  \nThe threat of the possible take over of the Watchers would have caused them to seeks lands where their ability to discuss and associate freely were unimpaired.\nRome had been controlling not only who could be citizens but who could visit as well.\nWhen Rome destroyed the second temple in Jerusalem, the diaspora that they created carried the Watchers along with the rest of the people as they had been embedded in society by using special buildings.\nThis diaspora would have spread the Watchers world-wide.\n</p>\n',3,'SqWMFvhFdx',15,'2020-05-22 16:46:24','2020-05-22 16:46:24',0),(52,'The Transfer of Knowledge ',1,'\n<p>Around 300 BC, Mayan cultural exploded with written script, astronomy and architecture.\nThis explosion was based on the Mayan\'s base 20 math system.\n</p>\n<p>The Watchers would have known of the existence of the Americas from the exploration crews sent out over the millennia.\nEach wave of Watchers exploring the world would have gone to an edge and then returned with their knowledge.\nThis slow collection would have enabled then to plan for future expansion and if necessary, escape to freer lands.\n</p>\n',4,'gg0xU2H1M3',15,'2020-05-22 16:46:24','2020-05-22 16:46:24',0),(53,'Volcanic Events ',1,'\n<p>When volcanoes erupt, they are grade on what is called the Volcanic Explosivity Index.  \nThis is a scale from 1 to 8.  An eruption of 6 or above is going to significantly effect the climate for a few years.\n</p><p>\nThe eruption which create the Year without a Summer (1815 - Tambora) was a 7 on the VEI.</p>\n<p>A partial list of eruptions during the Holocene:\n</p>\n',0,'ZN5VgkG0xQ',20,'2020-05-22 16:47:52','2020-05-22 16:47:52',0),(54,'Impact Events ',1,'\n<p>The frequency of impact events is inconclusive as to how often a history changer occurs.  \nThe climate effects comes from the impact ejaculate being blown into the atmosphere as if it were a volcanic event.\n</p><p>\nA potential measure would be the check the ammonia levels in the ice core caps to determine if there is a relationship to impact events and high levels.  \nThe level of the 535 impact event was the second highest of the last 2,000 year in the Greenland ice cores.  The highest in that time frame was at 1014 AD.\n</p>\n<p>A partial list of impact events for the Holocene:\n</p>\n',1,'LNn1rhjc2X',20,'2020-05-22 16:47:57','2020-05-22 16:47:57',0),(55,'Examining the Planet',1,'<p>As Gobkli Tepe changed with the progression of the Stars, a new location needed to be found. One of the first things done by the People is they sent out groups of people to examine the world.</p>\r\n<p>Planet wide, archaeologists have found stories of visitors around specific events and times in the past. In some places, the genes if not an actual visitor from a non-local region where found. I believe that there were several such fanouts: 8,000 BC, 7,000 BC and 6,000 BC. The 8,000 BC was evidenced in Stonehenge when test holes were found dating to around 8,100 BC. The 7,000 BC was evidenced by the appearance of Grapes in the middle east which could be used for wine production. The 6,000 BC is suggested by the Orion\'s Belts at Nabta Playa</p><p>.It is not inconceivable that pairs of old and younger \"Seekers\" went into the wilderness.  Knowledge of Stonehenge was acquired during the first waves of seekers. When the older reached their end, the would either instruct the younger to carry on and report or simply return and report where they got to when the elder died.</p>',10,NULL,4,'2020-05-22 18:27:48','2020-06-18 13:42:05',0),(56,'Egypt - the Prodigal Son',1,'<p>With the drying of the Sahara, all efforts to observe the skies moved to the Nile valley region especially Nekhen and Heliopolis. Heliopolis being the center of religious activity in the time of the Old Kingdom of Egypt.</p>\r\n<p>The eventual move of the Ben-Ben stone to Heliopolis from the Nabta Playa area closed the use of the depression for good. It is mentioned in the pyramid texts with a description of the dimpled stone being found along one of the sightings lines. This moving of the stone was done during the rainfall of Noah\'s Impact. This would have been the only time that travel to Naba Playa would have been possible. During normal times, a traveller must carry water to travel to the depression. During the fallout from Noah\'s Impact, the would have been a constant drizzle falling which could be collected to water people and animals.</p>\r\n<p>The appearance of Imhotep and his work on the pyramids where he laid out the eventual plans for the Great Pyramids. Imhotep\'s singular legacy was the logistics and technology of the internal ramp developed on the step pyramids. Jean-Pierre Houdin\'s \"internal ramp\" hypothesis﻿ has many intensely involved.  While the official story is that the ramp does not exist, the evidence mounts.</p><p>If we follow what has been said about Imhotep, then the following items were completed before the beginning of the construction of the Pyramids.</p><p></p><ul><li>Limestone facing</li><li>Raising food for workers</li><li>Warehouses for worker food and supplies</li><li>Logistics for food delivery</li><li>Logistics for stone delivery</li><li>Plans for taxation which do not cripple the economy</li></ul><p></p>\r\n<p>The Great Pyramids was laid out in an Orion\'s Belt fashion but dated 10,900 BC. The pyramids are by their size, the greatest of the ancient monuments.</p>',5,NULL,5,'2020-05-24 15:04:44','2020-07-05 17:14:55',0),(57,'Pyramid Texts',1,'<p>The texts are located in the pyramids of the Fourth and Fifth dynasties of Egypt. They present Egyptian heaven as a marsh land and reflect the soul of the departed into the night\'s sky over such a heaven.</p><p>Susan Brind Morrow[[dGgKUsXtCP]] in \'The Dawning Moon of the Mind: Unlocking the Pyramid Texts\' presents the texts as religious poem reflecting the beginning of Egyptian thought and religion.</p><p>Many of the passages of the story harken to a place such as Nabta Playa where the eastern horizon is unencumbered by obstacles especially fires. I believe that the text was created during the expedition to bring back the Benben stone. The only time that the depression would have been filled as a lake would have been Noah\'s Flood. Crossing the desert carrying water is cost prohibited at any time so water had to have been there for the expedition to be made.</p><p>The people on the expedition would have had stories as to the sequence of events starting with the filling of the rain, the rain\'s eventual evaporation and what would be left. The stories of how the Benben stone emerge from the muddy waters would have been seen and would have filled any poetic mind with song.</p>',4,NULL,5,'2020-05-26 18:36:01','2020-06-26 01:36:05',1),(59,'Battle of Jericho',0,'<p>The \'Battle of Jericho\' can be viewed as a cleansing of disease, specifically the plague.  \r\nBy the killing of every man, woman and child, the human vector of a disease dies.  \r\nThe elaborate cleanse after the battle is more in line with self-quarantine with the cleaning and waiting for a disease vector to take effect.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>This event also brings up dates of inconvenience.  \r\nMoses living to 120 year old had the experience and readiness of Joshua who lived to 110 years old.  \r\nThey were together during the Exodus and afterward in the desert.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Yet, they had to cleanse Jerico. \r\n</p>',1,NULL,12,'2020-06-17 15:47:25','2020-06-17 15:49:01',0),(60,'Pyramid Texts Revisited',1,'<p>The aftermath of the Impact created a favorable environment for explorations to Nabta Playa. Water would need to be carried by water from the atmospheric moisture would aid the expedition with soil that is not a yielding as sand is. Carrying water is the singular problem in the desert.</p>\r\n<p>During this period, an expedition was sent to Nabta Playa to retrieve the Benben Stone.</p>\r\n<p>During the expedition, the intermesh of old stories of the place, myths and the language of the desert boarding the sky would have provided a fertile ground for the creation of a Creation Myth. With the ephemeral existence of the environment at Nabta Playa, the emotions would prevail at a keeing level.</p>',7,NULL,7,'2020-06-24 15:59:20','2020-07-11 15:08:45',0),(61,'Bagnold\'s Stone Circle',0,'<p>A stone circle in the Libyan desert. It shows damage due to water.</p><p>The age of the circle has not been determined, but the damage due to water seems to indicate a date at least as old as the region that the circle is found in.</p><p>The similarity to the circle at Nabta Playa seems to indicate that the lunar calendar of the seasons matched with deep astrological knowledge at the basin.</p>',2,NULL,5,'2020-06-24 16:07:56','2020-06-26 14:08:52',1),(62,'Warren Fields - Calendar of the Moon',1,'<p>Warren Field is the oldest calendar in the world. It is near Crathes Castle, in the Aberdeenshire region of Scotland, in the United Kingdom.﻿</p><p>The various lunar calendars follow the mysterious Bagnold\'s Stone Circle, the calendar circle at Nabta Playa, the stone pins at Almendres, Portugal, all are examples of the investigation of earth/moon interaction.</p><p>The lunar calendar does not deal with procession as the solar calendar must.</p>',0,NULL,5,'2020-06-24 19:26:31','2020-06-26 14:11:35',1),(63,'Dogs',1,'<p>Dogs seem to have been domesticated by man twice. A western version and an eastern version. By 4,400 BC the eastern version was to only dog remaining.</p>',0,NULL,3,'2020-06-26 01:33:51','2020-06-28 20:23:43',1),(64,'Egyptian Mathematical Papyri',1,'<p>The exist today several papyruses relating to mathematics and the Egyptian world.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Moscow Mathematical Papyrus</li>\r\n<li>Lahun Mathematical Papyri</li>\r\n<li>Egyptian Mathematical Leather Roll</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p></p>',6,NULL,5,'2020-06-26 01:40:54','2020-06-26 14:04:27',1),(65,'Bible Version',1,'The version of the bible used here is the New International Version (NIV). It is clear and accurate. This is an issue as there exists an English Language version of the Bible altered to say that Mary was raped. The original Aramaic says no such thing.',0,NULL,6,'2020-06-26 16:57:35','2020-06-28 15:00:28',1),(66,'Younger Dryas',1,'The Younger Dryas is named after a tiny flower which appeared in various areas during the cold period. It is named after an indicator genus, the alpine-tundra wildflower Dryas octopetala.&nbsp; Its leaves are occasionally abundant in late glacial, often minerogenic-rich sediments, such as the lake sediments of Scandinavia.',3,NULL,3,'2020-06-30 16:46:42','2020-06-30 16:47:03',1),(67,'Destruction of Sodom and Gomorrah ',1,'<p>Santorini/Thera had two minor eruptions before exploding.  The first eruption cast a plume trace to the northeast of the \r\nMediterranean.  Traces of the plume have been found in Turkey and parts of Lebanon.  The second eruption was towards the\r\nsouth east over the land of Israel.  Abraham  in the plains of Mamre would have seen the first eruption as something \r\ndivine and safe as no fallout from the plume reached his location.  The intervening months between the first and second\r\neruptions would have allowed time for news of the destruction caused by the fallout of the first explosion to filter to \r\nAbraham.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>When the second eruption occurred and the plume came overhead, Abraham was visited by people who survived the first plume.\r\nThese survivors were surely angles having survived by being on God\'s side.  They sought to warm Lot, his family and friends\r\nthat the fallout from the plume could destroy them.  Who or what the angles sent to Lot in Sodom is unknowable.\r\nThere effect on the crowd at Sodom seems real enough.  If something or someone is brought to the city with knowledge\r\nof what is happening with the eruption plume overhead would be very sought after. Unless that city is one where they chop\r\nyou to pieces if you speak bad of the city.  Predicting Doom would be bad so Lot tired to protect them.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nSteven Collins\' work at Tall el-Hammam in Jordon has shown that the city he found matches the description of Sodom\r\nas defined in the Bible.  During the work of excavation, large quantities of glass where found that resemble Trinitite\r\nindicating a very hot explosion.  That the glass was located in a area covering Tall el-Hammam suggests to me a \r\nvolcanic cinder bomb not cooling correctly as it comes down resulting in a superheated explosion on a limited scale.\r\n</p>',8,NULL,9,'2020-07-09 18:05:53','2020-07-15 16:12:58',0),(68,'1,628 BC - Santorini - an Inconvenient Event ',1,'<p>This single event has influenced history and religion than any other.  \r\nThe explosion that came when Santorini/Thera finally blew.  \r\nDuring the set of eruptions, the eruption plumb was towards the northeast.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>The second set of eruptions was toward the southeast over the Dead sea and Egypt.  \r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The 10 Plagues of Egypt are in fact events resulting from the explosion. </li>\r\n<li>The occupation of mainland Greece by the Ekwesh Sea Peoples in 1,600 BC replacing those peoples destroyed by the tsunamis from Santorini.﻿</li><li>The destruction of Sodom and Gomorrah by a pyrolytic bomb spit out by the eruption.</li></ul><ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>These events bring into question the begets of the Bible and when did a particular individual exist.  \r\nThe 10 Plagues set in motion the Exodus according to the Bible, yet research is pointing to Moses being born after the Plagues and before the Exodus.</p><p>It is not clear as to when the Israelites left Egypt after the Plagues.  \r\nThe first objective event after the wandering in Desert is the Battle of Jericho after the Exodus.\r\nThis event again proves inconvenient.  \r\nIt has been dated to between 1,600 BC and 1,500 BC while the best date I can find for Moses is 1,572 BC - 1,451 BC.</p>',4,NULL,9,'2020-07-09 18:11:06','2020-07-15 01:32:03',0),(69,'Mystery Plays and the Revival of Ancient Religions ',NULL,'\n<p>\nThe Mystery Plays of the Greeks are a major ethical and religious stream of consciousness in the Western Civilization.\nYet the origin of these plays are a mystery.\nThey have no prior works in Greece that hold any pattern to what was written during the 6th century BC.\nIt has been argued that Greece\'s philosophical heritage came from Egypt during the 7th century BC.\nIndeed Plato\'s ancestor Solon went to Egypt and returned with the story of Atlantis.\n</p>\n',4,NULL,13,'2020-07-09 18:16:52','2020-07-09 18:16:52',0),(70,'Umm al Bini',0,'<p>The discovery of Umm al Bini was a fluke of war. Sadam Hussine had drained the great lake that sat atop the crater exposing it to satellite photography.</p><p>I call this the Cause of the Confusion of Civilization as there are two floods in this region. Noah\'s flood a thousand year before and now the Babylonian flood.</p><p>This flood was not as world wide as Noah\'s but left a distinct mark in history. In the digs in Iraq, there is a layer of mud over remains. The area of Umm al Bini would have been ocean estuary in 2,300BC\'s so the impact was more a mud spatter than a real water impact. Tree ring dating places this event at 2,354 BC with a 9 year window of cold weather.</p>',0,NULL,8,'2020-07-09 23:01:19','2020-07-09 23:01:41',1),(71,'Inconvenient Dates',0,'<p>Inconvenient dates refer to dates which can not be verified. The dates for the peoples of the Bible are particularly hard to interpret. The dates here are based on the eruption of Santorini and are \"squashy\" in that they could change if more evidence shows that the eruption occurred later or sooner that thought.</p><p>Here our dates are based on a physical event and an analysis of the Bible and Joseph. The main idea is that the seven years of darkness and famine as dreamed by the pharaoh is the aftermath of Santorini\'s eruption. This allows us to define a window in which Joseph would have been in Egypt.</p>',0,NULL,9,'2020-07-09 23:10:43','2020-07-09 23:10:54',1),(72,'Floods',1,'<p>Mega floods are different creatures. According to tradition several flood have been experienced.&nbsp; Mostly local or regional but not global.&nbsp; Noah\'s flood is different in that it was experienced regionally very extremely and globally with massive rains.</p><p><ul><li>Younger Dryas Mega flood</li><li>Flooding of regions on the plains by Greece</li><li>Kicked out of Eden - Flooding of the Black Sea</li><li>Noah\'s Flood</li><li>Babylonian Flood of Gilgamesh</li></ul></p>',0,NULL,7,'2020-07-11 15:08:35','2020-07-13 23:03:55',1),(73,'Volcano vs. Caldera',1,'<p>A volcano is a rupture in the crust of the Earth or other massive planetary body. It has a magma chamber beneath it. Where the magma chamber meets the exist to the surface is called the mouth. A Caldera is when the volcano collapses into the magma chamber at the mouth.</p>',3,NULL,9,'2020-07-15 01:30:49','2020-07-15 22:41:49',1),(74,'Ipuwer Papyrus',0,'Ipuwer Papyrus is a papyrus which describes invasion by Asiatics and rivers of blood.&nbsp; It is used by many for the Exodus IIt is better suited to describe the aftermath of Santorini\'s eruption.',5,NULL,9,'2020-07-15 16:12:40','2020-07-15 22:41:20',1),(75,'Trinitite',1,'Trinitite is the glassy residue left on the desert floor after the plutonium-based Trinity nuclear bomb test on July 16, 1945, near Alamogordo, New Mexico.',9,NULL,9,'2020-07-15 16:21:13','2020-07-15 16:21:24',1);
